<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Outside of home areas...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Malark">Malark</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:20 p.m. 11/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Outside of home areas...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I'm being dragged ever closer to the PvP server and am doing more research still. My question is, what's it like in the more open areas and far to reach dungeons? Like East Commonlands, West Commonlands, Befallen, The Desert of Ro, and the Karana Plains where there is the most intermixing of races? Is there a mostly an unspoken peace with people eyeing each oher warily and staying out of the way? Or do bands of vigilantes roam the areas killing anyone they see (I know its not THAT bad, I'm just using an extreme). What about places like Befallen, Crushbone, Cazic-Thule, and Guk? Is there an uneasy truce between bands of adventurers who know how easy it is for a fight to turn into a pellmell run to the exit? How hard is it to get higher of level when most of the bigger monsters are in relatively neutral areas?

<P>Malark, currently on Karana
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
